        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Live colonies of Unomia stolonifera (Gohar, 1938) on the reef of Vale Seco, Cunamá Bay, Estado Sucre, Venezuela. (A) Colonies with distinct polyp-bearing region; (B) Polyp featuring elongate dark brown tentacles due to the symbiotic zooxanthellae; (C–D) Individual polyps found below the level of the polyp-bearing region." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4709517/files/figure.png" .

