<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4709509>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Unomia stolonifera (Gohar, 1938) (A) Type BMNH 1889.5.27 consists of five colonies attached by a spreading membrane to skeleton fragments of branched Acropora stony coral; (B) Same type colonies viewed from the opposite side showing the spreading membrane. The colonies ramify into short branches, each with a polyp-bearing region. Individual polyps are also found on the branches below the polypary; (C) RMNH.COEL. 42436 and (D). RMNH.COEL. 42437 from Sulawesi, Indonesia; (E) ZMTAU Co. 38081 from Valle Seco, Bahia Conoma, Estado Sucre, Venezuela. All scale bars 1 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4709509/files/figure.png" .

